The detective work (the term was used by Ochoa, mail of 
05-02-2023
) carried on the initial description and the subsequent papers shows the interest of the historical perspective. Even if Oudemans was “a man of the old school” (

), the importance of the palp was already outlined in entomology two century ago and the first drawing of the tydeid palp was released in 1894. The reduction of the palpal chaetotaxy was thus unexpected, to say the least,

to Oudemans who knew the usual state of the palp. In contrast, the first complete phanerotaxy of the tydeid legs was published much later, only in 1938, and was introduced in tydeid taxonomy in 1965. This approach illustrates the way that, when we look back into the past with modern techniques and equipment (

) and current ideas (

), biases and misinterpretations can occur.

